<seg id=1> China's Insurance Supervision Program started in Beijing. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency. Beijing. Jan. 21. Several days ago, started in Beijing a research program aiming to help the People's Bank of China keep watch on the insurance regulations made by foreign-funded insurance setups in China, and to explore standardised insurance system and measures. </seg>
<seg id=3> This program is co-sponsored by British Royal Sun Alliance Insurance Co. Group and American Lincoln National Co. Group, undertaken by American Eternal Accountants Office. The total investment is $1.4 million. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> This insurance supervision program will systematically analyse China's foreign-investeded insurances as well as the existing laws and regulations on insurance supervision, and use foreign advanced experience for reference, and make a constructive research plan beneficial to the development of China's insurance supervision, and to the improvement of supervision laws and regulations . </seg>
<seg id=5> This insurance supervision program will make a further study on the basis of the existing laws and regulations of the People's Bank of China for supervising foreign-invested insurance organisations . It is devoted to strengthen the management of the organizations and operating processes, especially to develope an early alert system. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> It is said that the new supervision laws and regulations will improve the supervision system for the existing foreign-invested insurance setups in Chinese market, and meanwhile to help the People's Bank of China strengthen the supervision system for the whole insurance market. </seg>
</p>
